reference/
bin/
dist/
tmpbin/
# `make consumer-dryrun` leaves this binary in-tree as a side effect of
# `go build ./...` from inside the mini-module.
tools/consumer-dryrun/agent-director-consumer-dryrun
# Repo-root `go build ./...` drops the main-package binaries next to go.mod.
# These are build artifacts (not source) — installable via `make install`.
/agent-director
/cabi
/check-doccomments

# Bee hives live in the enclosing project folder, not the repo. Only the
# testplans hive (consumed by the Docker harness) stays in-tree. If a future
# `tickets/<Other>/` directory appears inside the repo it should NOT be
# committed — the hive belongs outside.
tickets/*
!tickets/testplans/
!tickets/testplans/**

# macOS Finder cruft
.DS_Store

# Test stub binaries — built by `make fake-tmux` / `make ts-helper`.
test/fake-tmux/tmux
